    • ifCase

      public ConditionalCallScenarioConsumerDefinition<S,M>.Branch<ConditionalCallScenarioConsumerDefinition<S,M>> ifCase(Predicate<ScenarioOrchestrationContext<M>> predicate)
      Attaches and changes scope to a conditional branch that is only executed if the given predicate matches at runtime for an integration call of the underlying scenario.

      This can be compared to a Java if-statement, and the returned branch allows to attach additional (conditional) branches similar to else if and else.

      To leave the conditional statement and return to the current scope, use ConditionalCallScenarioConsumerDefinition.Branch.endCases().

      Parameters:
      predicate - Predicate to test for execution of branch statmeents
      Returns:
      The conditional branch
      See Also:
      • ConditionalCallScenarioConsumerDefinition.Branch
      • ConditionalCallScenarioConsumerDefinition.Branch.elseIfCase(Predicate)
      • ConditionalCallScenarioConsumerDefinition.Branch.elseCase()

    • callAnyUnspecifiedScenarioConsumer

      public CallScenarioConsumerCatchAllDefinition<R,M> callAnyUnspecifiedScenarioConsumer()
      Specifies that any scenario consumer (which includes outbound connectors) that is attached to the integration scenario but not explicitly defined above will be called.

      This is a terminal operation for the consumer call specifications, so it needs to be the last call in the list and no additional consumers calls can be specified afterward.

      Returns:
      DSL handle for further call instructions

    • endDefinitionForThisProvider

      public R endDefinitionForThisProvider()
      Ends the orchestration-definitions for this provider and returns to the previous scope
      Returns:
      Previous scope
